jain kim transformative learning technologies laboratory home about publications projects people teaching media fablearn 2011 home people jain kim jain kim position alumni website website jain kim is a designer and educator from south korea and a master's student at stanford university in the learning design and technology program she has been working in and around the field of design in tokyo japan and mainly in seoul korea she is interested in searching for better ways to bring a designerly way of thinking to everyday life especially in classrooms to motivate and enhance learning in meaningful ways she is involved in a tltl project with colin meltzer and shima salehi process pad focusing on bringing the process to the foreground of every learning experience using interactive multimedia technology jain has a bfa in design from seoul national university seoul korea and a ma in design futures from university of london goldsmiths london united kingdom people faculty visiting researchers phd students ma students ms students undergraduate students high school interns collaborators alumni transformative learning technologies lab school of education stanford university 520 galvez mall room 102 ceras building stanford california 94305 usa connect with us connect with us on facebook connect with us on twitter connect with us on youtube connect with us on flickr copyright 2011 all rights reserved top
